#let abstract = [
  The Internet of Things (IoT) enables large-scale interconnection of heterogeneous devices, but this introduces significant challenges in terms of security and access control. This work presents the design and implementation of a trust-based authorization system for the MQTT protocol, one of the most widely used communication standards in IoT. The proposed solution extends the HiveMQ broker to integrate a trust model that evaluates device reliability based on attributes such as latency, error rate, connection security, and inter-device reputation. These attributes are combined through fuzzy logic to compute a global trust value, which is then applied in an Attribute-Based Access Control (ABAC) system. To complement the solution, a web application was developed with Svelte and TypeScript to manage and visualize system parameters, as well as an MQTT client and the server logic, both implemented in Java.
]
